
[1]pomegranate

   POMEGRAN'ATE, n. [L. pomum, an apple, and granatum, grained. See Grain
   and Granate.]

   1. The fruit of a tree belonging to the genus Punica. This fruit is as
   large as an orange, having a hard rind filled with a soft pulp and
   numerous seeds. It is of a reddish color.

   2. The tree that produces pomegranates.

   3. An ornament resembling a pomegranate, on the robe and ephod of the
   Jewish high priest.
